<article id="post-862" class="post-862 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-trains tag-c-train tag-calgary-transit tag-underground">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/11/west-lrt-line-in-calgary-approved/" rel="bookmark">West LRT Line in Calgary approved</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>It&#8217;s official &#8212; <a href="http://www.cbc.ca/canada/calgary/story/2007/11/20/west-lrt.html">I&#8217;m going to be able to ride the C-Train to work in four years</a>. Sounds like a long time away, but the reality is that this is going to make my life a lot better. Back when I used to live in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunnyside,_Calgary">Sunnyside</a>, I periodically took the C-Train to work &#8212; though it was really more like cheating given the short distance.<br />
But I&#8217;m almost back to driving to try and make up 30 minutes a day from travelling on buses and waiting for them to show up (basically, a 1.5 hour round-trip commute). This would help since the trains run near-constantly during rush hour, and cut down on the amount of walking I have to do!<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2007/11/west-lrt-line-in-calgary-approved/#more-862" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;West LRT Line in Calgary approved&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
